WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:02:22.033 --> 00:02:22.951
Hello. Quinn.

3
00:02:24.536 --> 00:02:26.579
Good morning. Quinn.
How's it going. mate?

4
00:02:26.746 --> 00:02:29.249
- What's up. guys?
- Working the late shift. are you?

5
00:02:29.791 --> 00:02:31.793
Ha! Someone's got to
clean up after you guys.

6
00:02:44.113 --> 00:02:45.531
Alright. Quinn.

7
00:02:45.615 --> 00:02:47.241
Oi. oi. oi.
Come on. then.

8
00:02:48.935 --> 00:02:50.395
You're not havin' one
yourself. then?

9
00:02:50.562 --> 00:02:52.105
No.
I'm trying to cut back.

10
00:02:57.152 --> 00:02:59.321
You heard from the school.
then. didn't you?

11
00:03:00.697 --> 00:03:02.032
Down you go.

12
00:03:20.983 --> 00:03:22.985
Good night. lads.

13
00:03:23.069 --> 00:03:25.071
- See you. Karen.
- Great work. Have a good weekend.

14
00:03:25.154 --> 00:03:26.989
Oi. Karen.
here's the new recruit.

15
00:03:27.073 --> 00:03:29.492
- Employment office is up top.
- Hi. Mum!

16
00:03:29.575 --> 00:03:31.577
Quinn. how are you. mate?

17
00:03:33.329 --> 00:03:34.789
Have you been smoking?

18
00:03:34.872 --> 00:03:37.500
No. I told you... I only smoke
when I've been drinking.

19
00:03:39.043 --> 00:03:40.211
What's wrong?

20
00:03:40.294 --> 00:03:41.254
Nothing.

21
00:03:41.337 --> 00:03:44.048
Quinn... what is it?

22
00:03:50.721 --> 00:03:53.516
You've got something
you want to show me.

23
00:04:10.908 --> 00:04:12.785
You know what it says.

24
00:04:16.998 --> 00:04:21.502
Scholarship was worth...
�3.000 a year.

25
00:04:21.586 --> 00:04:24.422
We don't have
that sort of money.

26
00:04:24.505 --> 00:04:26.090
Maybe we could ask Dad
to pay.

27
00:04:29.385 --> 00:04:30.887
Sorry.

28
00:04:30.970 --> 00:04:31.929
Karen?

29
00:04:32.013 --> 00:04:32.972
What?

30
00:04:33.055 --> 00:04:34.557
Got a problem at number 4.

31
00:04:34.640 --> 00:04:37.560
Jess says he's hit
some sort of a void.

32
00:04:57.246 --> 00:05:00.374
Oh. that bitch hasn't a clue
to what she's doing.

33
00:05:02.752 --> 00:05:05.463
Hey... Quinn.

34
00:05:05.546 --> 00:05:08.841
And what brings you
to the arsehole of the world?

35
00:05:08.925 --> 00:05:11.552
You're passing through it.
What's that make you?

36
00:05:14.388 --> 00:05:15.973
Here.

37
00:05:16.057 --> 00:05:18.226
Why don't you go inside
and have a wee look?

38
00:05:55.346 --> 00:05:57.181
Wicked.

39
00:06:44.729 --> 00:06:46.939
- I know it's still...
- Well. I covered it.

40
00:06:47.023 --> 00:06:48.191
What... Quinn!

41
00:06:49.775 --> 00:06:51.569
Mum. there's something
in there.

42
00:06:51.652 --> 00:06:52.945
There's something
in the hole!

43
00:06:53.029 --> 00:06:53.988
Damn it. Jess!

44
00:06:54.071 --> 00:06:55.448
It's unsafe conditions!

45
00:06:55.531 --> 00:06:57.325
Here.
Let's look at this void.

46
00:06:57.408 --> 00:06:59.076
It's unsafe!

47
00:06:59.160 --> 00:07:01.871
I'm just going to wash
your eyes out. okay?

48
00:07:01.954 --> 00:07:03.414
Mum. we've got to go!

49
00:07:03.498 --> 00:07:05.166
No. no.
We've got to do this fast.

50
00:07:05.249 --> 00:07:07.835
Open your eyes.
Open them up. Open them.

51
00:07:13.966 --> 00:07:15.218
Give me that.

52
00:07:32.318 --> 00:07:33.361
Get in!

53
00:07:40.868 --> 00:07:42.745
Mum. there was something
in there!

54
00:07:45.706 --> 00:07:47.583
Come here!

55
00:07:52.088 --> 00:07:54.215
Come on! Come on!

56
00:07:57.426 --> 00:07:58.136
Mum!

57
00:08:16.696 --> 00:08:17.947
Mum?

58
00:08:35.673 --> 00:08:37.675
I've kept this for years.

59
00:08:37.758 --> 00:08:39.969
because someday
it will be up to you.

60
00:08:40.052 --> 00:08:42.638
I don't want you to be afraid.

61
00:08:42.722 --> 00:08:44.515
I want you to understand.

62
00:08:46.684 --> 00:08:49.312
Knowledge is the only weapon
we've got left.

63
00:08:49.395 --> 00:08:52.440
In the beginning. it was
ignorance that destroyed us.

64
00:08:52.523 --> 00:08:55.776
I saw the first. but soon
the world saw millions.

65
00:08:55.860 --> 00:08:58.070
No one knew how they spawned
so fast.

66
00:08:58.154 --> 00:08:59.822
They swarmed like locusts.

67
00:08:59.906 --> 00:09:02.158
burning everything
in their path.

68
00:09:02.241 --> 00:09:04.494
driven by one purpose...
to feed.

69
00:09:04.577 --> 00:09:07.497
Even then. we couldn't believe
they were real.

70
00:09:07.580 --> 00:09:10.041
Ancient man had made them
into myths.

71
00:09:10.124 --> 00:09:13.169
but nature had made something
far more terrible.

72
00:09:13.252 --> 00:09:16.464
Too late. our scientists
discovered their true identity...

73
00:09:16.547 --> 00:09:20.218
a species which had burnt
the dinosaurs to dust.

74
00:09:20.301 --> 00:09:23.012
whose ash had brought on
ice ages.

75
00:09:23.095 --> 00:09:27.141
who. in aeons past. had
scorched the world clean of life.

76
00:09:27.225 --> 00:09:29.602
then starved. then slept.

77
00:09:29.685 --> 00:09:32.188
waiting for the Earth
to replenish itself.

78
00:09:32.271 --> 00:09:35.316
- 5... 4... 3...
- waiting to start their cycle anew.

79
00:09:35.399 --> 00:09:38.110
- 2... 1.
- Our weapons shot fire back at them.

80
00:09:38.194 --> 00:09:39.904
yet for every one of them
killed.

81
00:09:39.987 --> 00:09:41.572
a hundred took its place.

82
00:09:41.656 --> 00:09:43.741
They seemed invulnerable.

83
00:09:45.326 --> 00:09:48.329
We could only look on
as our leaders used

84
00:09:48.412 --> 00:09:50.581
their greatest arsenal
to destroy them.

85
00:09:50.665 --> 00:09:52.625
But in the end.
we only helped them.

86
00:09:52.708 --> 00:09:54.794
till the world burnt

87
00:09:54.877 --> 00:09:58.214
and the few of us
that were left fled the cities.

88
00:09:58.297 --> 00:10:00.716
found shelter where we could.

89
00:10:00.800 --> 00:10:03.511
You have to understand
our past

90
00:10:03.594 --> 00:10:05.638
because you will decide
our future.

91
00:10:05.721 --> 00:10:07.932
They're starving now.

92
00:10:08.015 --> 00:10:10.059
and they're more dangerous
than ever.

93
00:10:10.143 --> 00:10:12.436
But we have to go on.

94
00:10:12.520 --> 00:10:15.189
We have to outlast them.

95
00:10:15.273 --> 00:10:18.609
Only one species is getting out
of this alive.

96
00:10:34.834 --> 00:10:36.335
Hey. Quinn!

97
00:10:36.419 --> 00:10:39.088
Come and have a look
at this!

98
00:10:39.172 --> 00:10:41.674
It's a straight drop now
from the water tower.

99
00:10:41.757 --> 00:10:43.301
You just pull the plug.

100
00:10:43.384 --> 00:10:45.595
500 gallons per minute
hits the walls.

101
00:10:48.181 --> 00:10:50.099
I care about the specs.
Jerry.

102
00:10:50.183 --> 00:10:52.393
1.200 centigrade...
can it take it?

103
00:10:52.477 --> 00:10:54.437
Yeah. Course it can.

104
00:10:54.520 --> 00:10:57.148
Remember. I used to build
blast furnaces for a living.

105
00:10:57.231 --> 00:10:58.816
I know all about fire.

106
00:10:58.900 --> 00:11:01.068
Of course you do.
Sorry. mate.

107
00:11:01.152 --> 00:11:02.195
Nice one.

108
00:11:17.794 --> 00:11:19.796
Eddie's gone psycho.

109
00:11:19.879 --> 00:11:21.130
- Jared?
- Yeah. Quinn?

110
00:11:21.214 --> 00:11:23.633
Keep 'em at it.
No slacking!

111
00:11:23.716 --> 00:11:25.635
You heard him.
No slacking.

112
00:11:25.718 --> 00:11:27.094
Go!

113
00:11:33.184 --> 00:11:35.895
...I shall always walk.

114
00:11:35.978 --> 00:11:37.897
Ye. though
his brethren rose

115
00:11:37.980 --> 00:11:40.525
like locusts
from the Earth. Quinn.

116
00:11:40.608 --> 00:11:42.360
- no weapon could save me!
- Yeah.

117
00:11:42.443 --> 00:11:44.779
- No fire could extinguish theirs!
- Yeah.

118
00:11:44.862 --> 00:11:47.323
- They will prepare...
- Cheers. mate.

119
00:11:50.284 --> 00:11:51.786
What's up. Quinn?

120
00:12:15.560 --> 00:12:17.353
What are you doing. Eddie?

121
00:12:17.436 --> 00:12:20.857
Me and a few others.
we're going harvesting. Quinn.

122
00:12:20.940 --> 00:12:22.233
No. you're not.

123
00:12:22.316 --> 00:12:24.193
It's not ready.
We spoke about this.

124
00:12:24.277 --> 00:12:27.113
Half the stuff's not ripe. You
pick it now. it won't germinate.

125
00:12:27.196 --> 00:12:29.949
That means no seeds. That means
nothing to plant next season.

126
00:12:30.032 --> 00:12:32.326
There won't be a next season.
We'll be starved to death.

127
00:12:32.410 --> 00:12:34.245
What is this?
We can do it. Eddie.

128
00:12:34.328 --> 00:12:36.289
We decided. all of us.
you as well...

129
00:12:36.372 --> 00:12:39.625
dig in. work together.
outlast them.

130
00:12:39.709 --> 00:12:42.503
Kids can't eat hope. Quinn.
Edinburgh's gone.

131
00:12:42.587 --> 00:12:45.423
We haven't heard from Pembury
or Norwich in two years!

132
00:12:45.506 --> 00:12:47.717
We're on our own. Quinn.

133
00:12:47.800 --> 00:12:51.554
<i>Yeah. we know that. That's why we have
to hang on. Maybe we are all that's left.</i>

134
00:12:51.637 --> 00:12:54.724
Eight years I've listened
to you. and for what?

135
00:12:54.807 --> 00:12:57.477
Two kids and a wife
buried on the road.

136
00:12:57.560 --> 00:12:59.812
I'm not losing these.
Quinn.

137
00:12:59.896 --> 00:13:01.314
not when there's food
out there.

138
00:13:01.397 --> 00:13:02.773
Sorry. Eddie.

139
00:13:02.857 --> 00:13:04.484
You're not going anywhere.

140
00:13:04.567 --> 00:13:06.652
- Give me the keys.
- You bloody take 'em from me.

141
00:13:07.779 --> 00:13:10.406
It's a community.
not a prison.

142
00:13:11.783 --> 00:13:14.619
Eddie... you can argue
as much as you like.

143
00:13:14.702 --> 00:13:16.621
It makes no difference.

144
00:13:16.704 --> 00:13:19.040
The point is.
if you go out those gates.

145
00:13:19.123 --> 00:13:20.792
then you jeopardise
this community...

146
00:13:20.875 --> 00:13:24.128
you can stay out there.
because you're not coming back.

147
00:13:26.923 --> 00:13:28.925
Alright.

148
00:13:29.008 --> 00:13:31.677
I'm keeping these.

149
00:13:44.232 --> 00:13:47.318
Hey. Quinn.

150
00:13:47.401 --> 00:13:49.987
You know.
I'm your best friend.

151
00:13:50.071 --> 00:13:53.199
and sometimes
even I don't like you.

152
00:13:57.120 --> 00:13:58.162
Sorry.

153
00:14:09.507 --> 00:14:12.009
"Join me."
the black knight says.

154
00:14:12.093 --> 00:14:15.054
"then we can end
this conflict forever. "

155
00:14:15.138 --> 00:14:17.098
Never!

156
00:14:21.102 --> 00:14:23.771
"I'll never join you."
the white knight says.

157
00:14:23.855 --> 00:14:25.857
"You killed my father. "

158
00:14:31.362 --> 00:14:32.738
Creedy!

159
00:14:34.657 --> 00:14:38.536
The black knight stares through
the holes in his shiny mask.

160
00:14:38.619 --> 00:14:42.665
and he speaks words that burn
into our hero's heart forever.

161
00:14:48.463 --> 00:14:51.340
"I... am your father. "

162
00:14:54.302 --> 00:14:55.553
No!

163
00:15:01.517 --> 00:15:04.020
Did you make that up.
Mr. Quinn?

164
00:15:04.103 --> 00:15:05.521
Course I did.

165
00:15:08.274 --> 00:15:10.109
Alright. kids.
Time for bed.

166
00:15:10.193 --> 00:15:12.445
- No! - One
more! - No!

167
00:15:12.528 --> 00:15:14.781
Tomorrow. No. no.
Prayers first.

168
00:15:16.115 --> 00:15:17.200
Tomorrow!

169
00:15:17.283 --> 00:15:18.618
- "The Lion King"!
- Yeah! - Yeah!

170
00:15:18.701 --> 00:15:21.370
Tomorrow!
Prayers first!

171
00:15:26.292 --> 00:15:28.377
Okay.

172
00:15:29.420 --> 00:15:31.339
Ready?

173
00:15:31.422 --> 00:15:33.758
What do we do
when we wake?

174
00:15:33.841 --> 00:15:38.012
Keep both eyes on the sky.

175
00:15:38.095 --> 00:15:40.348
What do we do
when we sleep?

176
00:15:40.431 --> 00:15:43.768
Keep one eye on the sky.

177
00:15:43.851 --> 00:15:46.062
What do we do
when we see them?

178
00:15:46.145 --> 00:15:49.106
Dig hard. dig deep.

179
00:15:49.190 --> 00:15:50.650
run for shelter.

180
00:15:50.733 --> 00:15:52.985
and never look back.

181
00:15:53.069 --> 00:15:54.237
Well done.

182
00:15:54.320 --> 00:15:55.279
Good night. guys.

183
00:15:55.363 --> 00:15:56.322
Bedtime.

184
00:15:57.824 --> 00:15:58.783
Bedtime!

185
00:15:58.866 --> 00:15:59.867
Good night.

186
00:16:02.537 --> 00:16:05.164
Why can't we stay up later?

187
00:16:25.893 --> 00:16:27.270
Michael?

188
00:16:27.353 --> 00:16:28.938
Quinn's asleep.

189
00:16:29.021 --> 00:16:31.315
I took the keys.
Let's go.

190
00:16:38.990 --> 00:16:41.701
You keep quiet.

191
00:17:57.235 --> 00:17:59.237
Hello. Liam.

192
00:17:59.320 --> 00:18:02.198
Willem says it's dragon breath.

193
00:18:02.281 --> 00:18:05.201
Don't you listen to him.
It's just the wind.

194
00:18:10.039 --> 00:18:11.499
Okay.

195
00:19:42.298 --> 00:19:44.217
Oh. God.

196
00:19:46.010 --> 00:19:47.970
Ajay. alarm.

197
00:19:59.899 --> 00:20:01.109
Take cover. kids.
Come on. now.

198
00:20:01.192 --> 00:20:02.360
There we go. then.

199
00:20:02.443 --> 00:20:04.028
Okay. children!

200
00:20:04.112 --> 00:20:06.614
Head up!
One at a time!

201
00:20:06.697 --> 00:20:07.865
1... 2...

202
00:20:07.949 --> 00:20:10.576
Single file.
Single file.

203
00:20:13.996 --> 00:20:16.332
Let's move!

204
00:20:16.415 --> 00:20:17.458
Right.

205
00:20:20.461 --> 00:20:23.172
Move the kids.
Let's go. Come on.

206
00:20:24.924 --> 00:20:26.050
Creedy?

207
00:20:26.134 --> 00:20:27.135
- Yeah?
- You got a count?

208
00:20:27.218 --> 00:20:28.302
Yeah. We're good.

209
00:20:28.386 --> 00:20:31.973
Quinn!

210
00:20:32.056 --> 00:20:33.432
In the field.

211
00:21:24.525 --> 00:21:25.401
Dragons!

212
00:21:25.485 --> 00:21:26.402
Go get Eddie.

213
00:21:55.556 --> 00:21:58.392
Rachel!

214
00:21:58.476 --> 00:21:59.727
I'm here!

215
00:22:00.853 --> 00:22:03.523
Devon!

216
00:22:03.606 --> 00:22:05.024
- Devon!
- Michael!

217
00:22:05.108 --> 00:22:07.068
- D... Where's Michael?
- Michael?

218
00:22:08.402 --> 00:22:10.321
Michael! Michael!

219
00:22:10.404 --> 00:22:11.447
You okay?

220
00:22:13.199 --> 00:22:14.951
- Where's Matt?
- He's dead.

221
00:22:16.577 --> 00:22:17.495
Eddie!

222
00:22:19.872 --> 00:22:21.833
Let's go! Move!

223
00:22:36.931 --> 00:22:38.975
- Come on! Go!
- Come on. Michael!

224
00:22:39.058 --> 00:22:41.394
Go! Move!

225
00:22:42.937 --> 00:22:44.355
Keep going! Come on!

226
00:22:59.662 --> 00:23:03.040
Dad... w-what'll we do?

227
00:23:03.124 --> 00:23:05.334
We're trapped!

228
00:23:17.722 --> 00:23:19.223
Come on!

229
00:23:19.307 --> 00:23:20.725
Go!

230
00:23:20.808 --> 00:23:22.852
- Move it!
- Hurry up!

231
00:23:22.935 --> 00:23:25.104
Go! Come on!
Quick!

232
00:23:27.982 --> 00:23:30.109
Get in there!
Get in!

233
00:24:12.860 --> 00:24:14.779
Devon!

234
00:24:14.862 --> 00:24:16.489
Come on. Creedy.
Come on. Creedy!

235
00:24:16.572 --> 00:24:18.991
- It's gonna blow up!
- Back up! Back up! Back up!

236
00:24:19.075 --> 00:24:20.952
Oh. my God! Back up!

237
00:24:21.035 --> 00:24:22.453
I'm going as fast as I can!

238
00:24:26.582 --> 00:24:29.710
Back up! Back up! Back up!

239
00:24:33.464 --> 00:24:35.258
Stop! Quinn. stop!

240
00:24:35.341 --> 00:24:37.301
- Let me bloody go!
- No!

241
00:24:43.641 --> 00:24:44.642
No. Quinn!

242
00:24:49.605 --> 00:24:50.731
Devon's there!

243
00:24:54.026 --> 00:24:55.486
Devon!

244
00:24:56.779 --> 00:24:57.864
Devon!

245
00:25:05.204 --> 00:25:07.039
He doesn't care about us.

246
00:25:07.123 --> 00:25:09.709
He just wants the damn ash
off that field.

247
00:25:38.196 --> 00:25:40.448
Creedy's one-and-only
black label.

248
00:25:40.531 --> 00:25:42.742
aged two weeks
in a steel barrel.

249
00:25:42.825 --> 00:25:44.994
Now. the secret's
swallowing fast.

250
00:25:45.077 --> 00:25:48.164
That way it just burns your
stomach and not your throat.

251
00:25:49.916 --> 00:25:51.918
Go on.

252
00:25:52.001 --> 00:25:53.503
Sip it and weep.

253
00:25:53.586 --> 00:25:54.962
Poor bastard.

254
00:25:57.715 --> 00:25:58.925
Who? Eddie?

255
00:25:59.008 --> 00:26:00.426
A father's not meant to bury
his kids.

256
00:26:00.510 --> 00:26:02.094
It's supposed to be
the other way around.

257
00:26:02.178 --> 00:26:03.262
Yeah. well.
he wouldn't have had to

258
00:26:03.346 --> 00:26:04.722
- if he'd just listened. would he?
- No.

259
00:26:04.806 --> 00:26:07.058
No. Creedy.
Maybe he was right.

260
00:26:07.141 --> 00:26:10.728
It's easy to square your shoulders
and bear it when you don't have kids.

261
00:26:11.938 --> 00:26:13.689
Maybe there won't be
another harvest.

262
00:26:13.773 --> 00:26:15.942
No. Not now.
with half the crop gone.

263
00:26:16.025 --> 00:26:18.402
God knows how we're
going to get through.

264
00:26:19.654 --> 00:26:22.573
You remember when we'd go out
and bring in 80%. 90% of it?

265
00:26:22.657 --> 00:26:24.242
Not anymore.

266
00:26:24.325 --> 00:26:26.744
Not in the last few years.

267
00:26:26.828 --> 00:26:28.412
They're hungrier. too.

268
00:26:28.496 --> 00:26:30.623
Hey...

269
00:26:30.706 --> 00:26:33.000
you're not giving up on me.
are you?

270
00:26:35.878 --> 00:26:38.297
No.

271
00:26:38.381 --> 00:26:40.633
I just thought
if we could hang on.

272
00:26:40.716 --> 00:26:43.219
somehow we'd make it
through.

273
00:26:55.982 --> 00:26:59.777
This is a national civil defence
alert for all who can hear this...

274
00:26:59.861 --> 00:27:02.655
...no choice but to authorise
the use of nuclear weapons...

275
00:27:26.721 --> 00:27:30.141
The sole survivor was
a 12-year-old boy...

276
00:27:41.068 --> 00:27:42.653
Roger that.

277
00:27:42.737 --> 00:27:45.698
I'm going in.
Stay high on my...

278
00:27:45.782 --> 00:27:47.909
charge all weapons.

279
00:27:51.329 --> 00:27:53.664
Hey. Barlow.
I've got voices.

280
00:27:53.748 --> 00:27:55.583
Ajay.
what are you smoking?

281
00:27:55.666 --> 00:27:57.376
I'm not messing
with you. Barlow.

282
00:27:57.460 --> 00:27:58.628
Take a look.

283
00:27:58.711 --> 00:28:00.838
A look at what?

284
00:28:00.922 --> 00:28:02.715
She's not moving.

285
00:28:02.799 --> 00:28:05.301
Forget the bird
and use the scope. you wanker.

286
00:28:18.481 --> 00:28:19.774
Oh. dear.

287
00:28:25.738 --> 00:28:28.366
Creedy!

288
00:28:28.449 --> 00:28:30.076
I've got to go.

289
00:28:34.997 --> 00:28:37.416
Alright. lads.
this isn't a drill!

290
00:28:39.585 --> 00:28:40.962
Move it along!

291
00:28:41.045 --> 00:28:42.964
Get those out.
One to Creedy.

292
00:28:43.047 --> 00:28:44.465
Another one to carry!

293
00:28:44.549 --> 00:28:46.968
Here's Creedy's.

294
00:28:47.051 --> 00:28:49.428
Alright. alright!
Come on. then! Come on!

295
00:28:49.512 --> 00:28:50.680
Extra shells!

296
00:28:52.014 --> 00:28:53.599
Come on!

297
00:28:53.683 --> 00:28:55.268
We haven't got all day!

298
00:29:26.424 --> 00:29:28.426
Marauders.

299
00:29:28.509 --> 00:29:30.803
Years since we've seen them.

300
00:29:32.805 --> 00:29:34.599
Well.
look on the bright side.

301
00:29:36.350 --> 00:29:39.145
At least we're not alone.

302
00:30:36.994 --> 00:30:40.915
Only one thing worse
than a dragon...

303
00:30:40.998 --> 00:30:42.625
Americans.

304
00:30:48.297 --> 00:30:50.174
Oh. what a dump.

305
00:30:55.513 --> 00:30:58.724
Who's in charge?!

306
00:31:01.352 --> 00:31:03.438
Well. that would be you.
then.

307
00:31:14.949 --> 00:31:18.202
Anything happens.
you know what to do.

308
00:31:19.328 --> 00:31:21.622
Uh. no.
I have no idea.

309
00:31:23.708 --> 00:31:24.834
Me neither.

310
00:31:46.230 --> 00:31:48.107
That's a big tank.

311
00:31:58.868 --> 00:32:01.078
You responsible
for this place?

312
00:32:01.162 --> 00:32:02.497
Who are you?

313
00:32:02.580 --> 00:32:04.957
Name's Van Zan.
Kentucky Irregulars.

314
00:32:05.041 --> 00:32:06.584
You're a long way from home.
Van Zan. You lost?

315
00:32:09.170 --> 00:32:12.131
Rebuilt a National Guard
C5A.

316
00:32:12.215 --> 00:32:16.010
Flew it 8.000 miles on 2
engines and tried to set it down

317
00:32:16.093 --> 00:32:19.430
on the old strip
outside of Manchester.

318
00:32:19.514 --> 00:32:23.184
Lost 122 men
and most of my fuel.

319
00:32:23.267 --> 00:32:26.020
We need shelter and a place
to refit artillery.

320
00:32:26.104 --> 00:32:28.523
We'll be out of your hair
by 1800 hours tomorrow.

321
00:32:28.606 --> 00:32:31.109
That's a good story. especially
the bit about the plane.

322
00:32:31.192 --> 00:32:33.319
but there hasn't been anything
in the air for 20 years.

323
00:32:33.402 --> 00:32:34.654
That's their territory.

324
00:32:35.738 --> 00:32:38.658
<i>It's my territory.
It's your territory.</i>

325
00:32:38.741 --> 00:32:40.034
They're just rentin' it.

326
00:32:40.118 --> 00:32:41.369
Turn around. Van Zan.

327
00:32:46.332 --> 00:32:48.835
Don't be a fool.

328
00:32:51.629 --> 00:32:54.757
We can do this easy...

329
00:32:54.841 --> 00:32:57.677
or we can do it
real easy.

330
00:33:04.267 --> 00:33:06.352
You try it.

331
00:33:10.731 --> 00:33:13.568
You ever seen
one of these?

332
00:33:13.651 --> 00:33:16.070
Not many men have.

333
00:33:16.154 --> 00:33:18.448
Got it off the first one
I killed.

334
00:33:20.616 --> 00:33:23.035
The plane was better.

335
00:33:23.119 --> 00:33:25.955
So now you're
a dragon killer.

336
00:33:26.038 --> 00:33:28.082
That's not even original.

337
00:33:28.166 --> 00:33:29.750
It was in a wheat field

338
00:33:29.834 --> 00:33:32.378
just south of Coffeyville.
Kansas.

339
00:33:33.588 --> 00:33:35.506
It was late November.

340
00:33:35.590 --> 00:33:37.467
It's a month of mist.

341
00:33:37.550 --> 00:33:39.552
And we were caught
in the open.

342
00:33:39.635 --> 00:33:41.637
The sun was setting
behind us.

343
00:33:41.721 --> 00:33:44.098
There was nowhere to run.

344
00:33:44.182 --> 00:33:46.267
Twice it came in on us.

345
00:33:46.350 --> 00:33:48.811
and twice it missed
the heart of us.

346
00:33:51.564 --> 00:33:56.444
And that's when I had
an epiphany.

347
00:33:56.527 --> 00:34:01.908
You see. they have
great vision... in the day.

348
00:34:01.991 --> 00:34:06.496
And they have
even better vision at night.

349
00:34:06.579 --> 00:34:12.418
But in the failing light.
they can't focus.

350
00:34:12.502 --> 00:34:14.337
Magic hour.

351
00:34:29.143 --> 00:34:31.062
Coffeyville.

352
00:34:31.145 --> 00:34:33.272
It's etched
in American history

353
00:34:33.356 --> 00:34:35.900
because the outlaw Dalton boys
were killed there.

354
00:34:35.983 --> 00:34:38.361
Ordinary townsfolk rose up
and took 'em down.

355
00:34:41.030 --> 00:34:43.324
Maybe you're
the Dalton boys.

356
00:34:43.407 --> 00:34:47.787
No. no...
we're the townsfolk.

357
00:34:56.963 --> 00:35:01.050
You try anything...

358
00:35:01.134 --> 00:35:03.344
I'll kill you.

359
00:35:06.264 --> 00:35:09.100
Didn't get your name.

360
00:35:09.183 --> 00:35:10.810
Quinn.

361
00:35:50.892 --> 00:35:52.852
Well...
I'm sure you've got

362
00:35:52.935 --> 00:35:55.480
a perfectly good
explanation for this.

363
00:35:55.563 --> 00:35:57.732
but I'm buggered
if I know what it is.

364
00:35:59.901 --> 00:36:01.486
He's a dragon slayer.

365
00:36:01.569 --> 00:36:03.237
A what?

366
00:36:03.321 --> 00:36:06.032
He's a dragon slayer!

367
00:36:06.115 --> 00:36:07.492
Oh. he's a dragon slayer.

368
00:36:07.575 --> 00:36:09.118
Oh. good.

369
00:36:09.202 --> 00:36:11.788
And I suppose that makes you
King Arthur. does it?

370
00:36:11.871 --> 00:36:14.165
Christ almighty. Quinn.

371
00:36:14.248 --> 00:36:15.875
I mean.
even if you believe that.

372
00:36:15.958 --> 00:36:18.294
and you'd have to be
an imbecile.

373
00:36:18.377 --> 00:36:21.172
- do you not think we'd be easy meat for these guys?
- You weren't there.

374
00:36:21.255 --> 00:36:22.799
Look at this guy.
Look. Look.

375
00:36:22.882 --> 00:36:24.884
I mean. he looks like...
like a... like a rogue Marine.

376
00:36:24.967 --> 00:36:27.094
You remember those guys?
Oh. yeah. sure.

377
00:36:27.178 --> 00:36:29.555
They blew up plenty of dragons
in their time.

378
00:36:29.639 --> 00:36:31.599
but they also took
half the world...

379
00:36:31.682 --> 00:36:33.726
You weren't there!
I saw his eyes. Creedy!

380
00:37:10.763 --> 00:37:14.308
Move it! Move it!
Move it!

381
00:37:37.790 --> 00:37:39.500
Great job.

382
00:37:39.584 --> 00:37:42.837
We ran a 30-mile grid
in every direction... nothing.

383
00:37:42.920 --> 00:37:45.089
Could be on the moon. Denton.

384
00:37:47.091 --> 00:37:52.054
Quinn. this is Alexandra
Jensen. U.S. Cavalry.

385
00:37:52.138 --> 00:37:53.556
Oh. Captain Creedy.

386
00:37:53.639 --> 00:37:54.932
Hey.

387
00:37:55.016 --> 00:37:56.642
How you doin'?
Creedy.

388
00:37:56.726 --> 00:37:58.186
Denton Van Zan.

389
00:37:58.269 --> 00:37:59.479
How are you?

390
00:37:59.562 --> 00:38:01.355
Excuse me.

391
00:38:01.439 --> 00:38:03.316
Who are they?

392
00:38:03.399 --> 00:38:05.777
Archangels.

393
00:38:06.903 --> 00:38:08.696
17 seconds...

394
00:38:08.780 --> 00:38:11.616
Once they jump from the chopper.
that's their life expectancy.

395
00:38:11.699 --> 00:38:14.410
You never thought
of giving them parachutes?

396
00:38:14.494 --> 00:38:16.454
They're not much help.
They're bulla men.

397
00:38:16.537 --> 00:38:18.998
What?

398
00:38:19.081 --> 00:38:22.835
They were used by gladiators
to snare other men.

399
00:38:22.919 --> 00:38:25.755
Not men. dragons.

400
00:38:25.838 --> 00:38:29.342
So. you guys. uh.
jump out the chopper

401
00:38:29.425 --> 00:38:32.678
and use a net
to snare dragons?

402
00:38:34.347 --> 00:38:35.973
Ha.
I mean. sure. yeah.

403
00:38:36.057 --> 00:38:38.601
I mean...
you would. wouldn't you?

404
00:38:53.658 --> 00:38:56.911
Three watches.
eight hours each.

405
00:38:56.994 --> 00:38:59.914
All the kids
in the shelter.

406
00:38:59.997 --> 00:39:02.083
Rifles on
the keep and walls.

407
00:39:02.166 --> 00:39:03.459
Excuse me.

408
00:39:03.543 --> 00:39:06.003
Aren't you forgetting
who let them in?

409
00:39:06.087 --> 00:39:09.173
Don't mean I trust 'em.

410
00:39:14.595 --> 00:39:17.557
Alright. guys.

411
00:39:33.239 --> 00:39:36.075
I just brewed a fresh pot. if
that's what you're looking for.

412
00:39:36.159 --> 00:39:38.703
A whetstone. actually.

413
00:39:42.415 --> 00:39:44.625
Sure.

414
00:39:49.630 --> 00:39:50.965
Is that your son?

415
00:39:51.048 --> 00:39:54.594
No.
Got him from the pound.

416
00:39:56.262 --> 00:39:58.848
Hmm. Is that where you
get all your children?

417
00:40:03.019 --> 00:40:04.854
I found him in a village
near Bray.

418
00:40:04.937 --> 00:40:07.356
3 years old.
sitting with his mum.

419
00:40:07.440 --> 00:40:09.650
He kept trying
to wake her up.

420
00:40:09.734 --> 00:40:13.112
She had been dead
for days.

421
00:40:13.196 --> 00:40:18.159
We were making our way up here. a
few of us... me. Creedy. and Barlow.

422
00:40:18.242 --> 00:40:20.286
No idea how
we were gonna survive.

423
00:40:20.369 --> 00:40:22.830
Anyway. I grabbed him.

424
00:40:22.914 --> 00:40:25.625
What else was I gonna do?

425
00:40:25.708 --> 00:40:27.877
Leave him.

426
00:40:27.960 --> 00:40:29.670
Most men would have...

427
00:40:29.754 --> 00:40:32.548
especially back
in the early years.

428
00:40:32.632 --> 00:40:35.092
Everybody's just running
for their lives.

429
00:40:35.176 --> 00:40:39.096
Yeah.
Well. I didn't.

430
00:40:39.180 --> 00:40:41.057
Regretted it ever since.
of course.

431
00:40:56.405 --> 00:40:59.075
What are you doing here?

432
00:41:01.494 --> 00:41:04.122
What do you want?

433
00:41:04.205 --> 00:41:08.501
You want to know anything.
you ask Van Zan.

434
00:41:36.237 --> 00:41:37.947
Goosh. you alive?!

435
00:41:38.030 --> 00:41:39.198
Not even close. Denton.

436
00:41:44.203 --> 00:41:46.289
Alex! Radios are down!

437
00:41:46.372 --> 00:41:48.958
Cover the east ridge
and tell me what you see!

438
00:41:49.041 --> 00:41:50.877
Men. get ready
to rock 'n' roll!

439
00:41:50.960 --> 00:41:52.295
We got a dragon to kill!

440
00:41:53.254 --> 00:41:55.298
- Goosh. set the triangulators!
- Roger that!

441
00:41:55.381 --> 00:41:58.718
Tito. Mead. Piscatella.
bounce your butts!

442
00:41:58.801 --> 00:42:01.846
Move out!

443
00:42:41.844 --> 00:42:43.805
Alex. what do you see?

444
00:42:45.598 --> 00:42:46.766
No sign of it.

445
00:42:46.849 --> 00:42:48.267
Visibility is about 3 miles
on the deck.

446
00:42:48.351 --> 00:42:50.394
Roger that.

447
00:42:50.478 --> 00:42:53.189
Stay on the deck
till I get the verticals up.

448
00:42:53.272 --> 00:42:55.691
Copy that. Van Zan.

449
00:42:55.775 --> 00:42:57.860
Waiting for triangulator.
Safety first. guys.

450
00:42:57.944 --> 00:43:00.571
Safety?! What part of this job
do you find safe?!

451
00:43:00.655 --> 00:43:03.157
It's not you I'm worried
about. It's my chopper.

452
00:43:03.241 --> 00:43:06.327
Oh. Cold.
Ha ha ha ha!

453
00:43:11.958 --> 00:43:13.501
First vertical's up.

454
00:43:13.584 --> 00:43:15.253
Vertical 1 up. Alex.

455
00:43:15.336 --> 00:43:16.963
Copy that.

456
00:43:26.806 --> 00:43:27.974
Second vertical is up.

457
00:43:28.057 --> 00:43:29.725
Second vertical is up. Alex.

458
00:43:29.809 --> 00:43:32.979
Now. once I have radar.
you go to 5.000 feet.

459
00:43:33.062 --> 00:43:35.982
Fly directly back
above my location.

460
00:43:36.065 --> 00:43:37.942
Gideon. you and the boys bring
that bitch right down on my head.

461
00:43:38.025 --> 00:43:39.360
and I'll take it from there.

462
00:43:39.444 --> 00:43:41.070
Copy that. Van Zan.

463
00:43:41.154 --> 00:43:43.197
Alvarez. you're the bait.

464
00:43:43.281 --> 00:43:44.657
Jefferson. you and I
are the gunners.

465
00:43:44.740 --> 00:43:46.284
We don't open our chutes

466
00:43:46.367 --> 00:43:50.538
until you give us confirmation
that it's down. right?

467
00:43:54.250 --> 00:43:56.335
Bogey on our tail.
200 yards!

468
00:43:56.419 --> 00:43:58.004
- Go. go. go. go!
- Roger!

469
00:43:58.087 --> 00:44:00.339
I'll try to lose it up
in the clouds.

470
00:44:08.806 --> 00:44:11.768
Piscatella. do you read me?

471
00:44:25.031 --> 00:44:28.034
God damn it. Piscatella!
Get your vertical up!

472
00:44:34.207 --> 00:44:36.501
Come on. number 3!
Piscatella. that's you!

473
00:44:36.584 --> 00:44:38.336
I'm almost there!

474
00:44:38.419 --> 00:44:40.213
I'm almost
at the top of the...

475
00:44:47.094 --> 00:44:48.679
God damn it. Piscatella.
Come in.

476
00:44:50.389 --> 00:44:51.933
Ajay?

477
00:44:52.016 --> 00:44:54.477
Can you hear anything?

478
00:44:54.560 --> 00:44:56.020
Van Zan's trying
to take it on. Quinn.

479
00:44:56.104 --> 00:44:57.814
using some kind
of 3-D mapping device.

480
00:44:57.897 --> 00:44:59.357
If they don't get
that third vertical up.

481
00:44:59.440 --> 00:45:01.109
Alex is flying blind.

482
00:45:08.991 --> 00:45:10.993
Come on!

483
00:45:12.912 --> 00:45:15.581
Van Zan. what's going on?

484
00:45:15.665 --> 00:45:18.334
I'm at altitude.
We're blind up here.

485
00:45:18.417 --> 00:45:22.130
Can you give me some time? I'm having
trouble with the third vertical.

486
00:45:25.091 --> 00:45:27.677
Come on. number 3!
Piscatella. that's you!

487
00:45:27.760 --> 00:45:28.928
Get your vertical up!

488
00:45:55.288 --> 00:45:56.414
Alright. Piscatella.

489
00:45:56.497 --> 00:45:57.540
Third vertical's up.

490
00:45:57.623 --> 00:45:58.749
Alex. we have visual.

491
00:46:00.626 --> 00:46:01.711
Monitor's coming up.

492
00:46:05.548 --> 00:46:08.050
Hold on!

493
00:46:08.134 --> 00:46:09.594
Alvarez!

494
00:46:16.225 --> 00:46:18.186
It's right on us!
It's right on us!

495
00:46:18.269 --> 00:46:20.104
Go. go. go. go.
go. go. go. go!

496
00:46:22.982 --> 00:46:25.943
Damn it!

497
00:46:26.027 --> 00:46:26.986
Talk to me. Alex!

498
00:46:27.069 --> 00:46:29.447
Angels are flying.

499
00:46:44.754 --> 00:46:47.340
Alex. do you have
a reading?!

500
00:46:49.759 --> 00:46:51.511
Okay. Target...
1.500 feet.

501
00:46:51.594 --> 00:46:55.556
Copy that. Alvarez.
do you have a visual?!

502
00:46:55.640 --> 00:46:57.058
Negative.

503
00:46:59.727 --> 00:47:01.938
Damn it! It's right on top of me! Shoot!

504
00:47:02.021 --> 00:47:04.107
Shoot at what?!
I can't see a thing!

505
00:47:08.402 --> 00:47:10.363
Nets away!

506
00:47:13.866 --> 00:47:15.243
Great shot!

507
00:47:15.326 --> 00:47:17.578
Alright. Jefferson!

508
00:47:17.662 --> 00:47:19.080
Roger that.

509
00:47:19.163 --> 00:47:21.290
Alvarez. can you see it?

510
00:47:21.374 --> 00:47:23.459
Negative.
I think it's down.

511
00:47:24.669 --> 00:47:26.337
Copy that.

512
00:47:27.380 --> 00:47:30.508
Shit! Alex. both nets
just flew right by me.

513
00:47:30.591 --> 00:47:33.594
Alvarez. can you confirm
that it is down?

514
00:47:34.428 --> 00:47:35.638
Copy that!

515
00:47:35.721 --> 00:47:39.767
Negative! It's on me!

516
00:47:56.033 --> 00:48:00.705
Jefferson. I'm not getting
any contact with Alvarez.

517
00:48:00.788 --> 00:48:02.165
Keep your eyes open.

518
00:48:02.248 --> 00:48:03.791
Roger that.

519
00:48:03.875 --> 00:48:05.877
- Jefferson. look out!
- Oh. my...

520
00:48:15.803 --> 00:48:18.014
Gideon's down.

521
00:48:19.348 --> 00:48:21.267
Piscatella.

522
00:48:21.350 --> 00:48:23.561
- Piscatella. do you read me?
- Van Zan.

523
00:48:23.644 --> 00:48:24.812
Who is this?

524
00:48:24.896 --> 00:48:25.855
Quinn.

525
00:48:25.938 --> 00:48:27.148
Quinn. where's Piscatella?

526
00:48:27.231 --> 00:48:29.192
- He's gone.
- Are you ready to ride?

527
00:48:29.275 --> 00:48:30.693
'Cause you got
about 30 seconds

528
00:48:30.777 --> 00:48:31.778
till the bitch
is on top of you.

529
00:48:31.861 --> 00:48:33.362
You bring her to me.

530
00:48:33.446 --> 00:48:36.365
You're the bait. Quinn.
1.600 pounds of horseflesh.

531
00:48:36.449 --> 00:48:39.035
Ride her right down my
throat. Do you read me?

532
00:48:39.118 --> 00:48:40.578
Ride the north road
to the quarry.

533
00:48:40.661 --> 00:48:42.038
Bring her to me. Quinn.

534
00:48:45.082 --> 00:48:46.667
I'm coming.

535
00:48:49.420 --> 00:48:51.422
Hmm? Here we go.

536
00:48:56.886 --> 00:48:58.221
Okay. Okay.

537
00:49:00.890 --> 00:49:03.017
Come on!

538
00:49:03.101 --> 00:49:07.855
Line up 20 yards
south by southwest!

539
00:49:07.939 --> 00:49:10.149
Come on!

540
00:49:18.449 --> 00:49:20.159
Come on!

541
00:49:23.955 --> 00:49:25.748
1.200 yards.

542
00:49:25.832 --> 00:49:29.293
Wind velocity... 10.2
north by northwest.

543
00:49:29.377 --> 00:49:31.671
Come on! Come on!

544
00:50:57.256 --> 00:50:59.050
Yeah. this is really
good stuff. Thanks.

545
00:50:59.133 --> 00:51:01.052
<i>I don't a-care about that</i>

546
00:51:01.135 --> 00:51:03.012
<i>- Got a new fool
- Hey. good day. Quinn. yeah?</i>

547
00:51:03.096 --> 00:51:05.014
<i>- I'd like to laugh at
- Alright. Quinn.</i>

548
00:51:05.098 --> 00:51:06.849
<i>I have only one
burning desire</i>

549
00:51:06.933 --> 00:51:08.434
Hats off to you. mate.

550
00:51:08.518 --> 00:51:10.311
- Yeah! - Yeah!
- Yeah! - Yeah!

551
00:51:22.073 --> 00:51:24.200
<i>...stand. baby</i>

552
00:51:24.283 --> 00:51:26.410
<i>Listen here. baby</i>

553
00:51:26.494 --> 00:51:29.372
<i>And stop actin' so crazy</i>

554
00:51:29.455 --> 00:51:30.957
<i>You say your mom ain't home</i>

555
00:51:31.040 --> 00:51:32.792
<i>It ain't my concern</i>

556
00:51:32.875 --> 00:51:34.335
<i>Just a-play with me</i>

557
00:51:34.418 --> 00:51:36.254
<i>And you won't get burnt</i>

558
00:51:36.337 --> 00:51:39.423
<i>I have only one
itchin' desire</i>

559
00:51:39.507 --> 00:51:42.468
<i>Let me stand next
to your fire</i>

560
00:51:42.552 --> 00:51:44.595
<i>Let me stand. yeah</i>

561
00:51:44.679 --> 00:51:47.306
<i>Let me stand. baby</i>

562
00:51:47.390 --> 00:51:48.683
<i>Let me stand</i>

563
00:52:02.738 --> 00:52:05.783
Envy the country
that has heroes. huh?!

564
00:52:12.290 --> 00:52:17.044
I say pity the country
that needs 'em.

565
00:52:19.714 --> 00:52:22.383
What are you celebrating?

566
00:52:22.467 --> 00:52:26.345
One dragon down.
three men dead? Oh. yeah.

567
00:52:26.429 --> 00:52:31.309
At that rate. we might just be
getting somewhere in about 320 years.

568
00:52:31.392 --> 00:52:34.353
Is that what you want?

569
00:52:34.437 --> 00:52:37.106
You want
a little accommodation?

570
00:52:37.190 --> 00:52:39.942
Unh-unh.

571
00:52:40.026 --> 00:52:42.779
These beasts live on ash.

572
00:52:42.862 --> 00:52:45.573
They feed on death.

573
00:52:45.656 --> 00:52:48.201
There's no middle ground...

574
00:52:48.284 --> 00:52:53.164
not for them. not for us.

575
00:52:53.247 --> 00:52:57.418
And sure as hell not for my men
who died out there today.

576
00:53:02.173 --> 00:53:05.927
But you go ahead.

577
00:53:06.010 --> 00:53:10.098
<i>Have your little... soiree.</i>

578
00:53:10.181 --> 00:53:13.392
Personally. you disgust me.

579
00:53:20.733 --> 00:53:23.319
We bury our dead at dawn.

580
00:54:37.018 --> 00:54:40.062
What are you doing here.
Quinn?

581
00:54:41.731 --> 00:54:45.860
You're standing on ground
where I've buried hundreds.

582
00:54:45.943 --> 00:54:47.403
This is my home.

583
00:54:47.487 --> 00:54:50.323
I'm asking the questions.

584
00:54:50.406 --> 00:54:51.783
<i>What are you doing here?</i>

585
00:54:53.951 --> 00:54:57.538
I lead... you follow.

586
00:55:17.600 --> 00:55:21.354
I kept these for you.

587
00:55:21.437 --> 00:55:24.065
They sent them off proud.
Alex.

588
00:55:24.148 --> 00:55:27.652
Alex is the keeper
of the dead. Quinn.

589
00:55:27.735 --> 00:55:29.153
She's our memory.

590
00:55:29.237 --> 00:55:30.822
When this thing is over.

591
00:55:30.905 --> 00:55:33.157
she's gonna build a wall
with those things.

592
00:55:33.241 --> 00:55:36.077
And. unfortunately. it's
gonna be a very long wall.

593
00:55:36.160 --> 00:55:38.121
I'm out of resources.
Quinn.

594
00:55:38.204 --> 00:55:40.373
I'm out of men.

595
00:55:40.456 --> 00:55:42.708
Alex. tell him.

596
00:55:42.792 --> 00:55:45.962
- Did you see the one we brought down. the big bull?
- Yeah.

597
00:55:46.045 --> 00:55:48.464
Well. it wasn't.
It was a female.

598
00:55:48.548 --> 00:55:51.467
There was at least one egg.
probably more.

599
00:55:51.551 --> 00:55:54.846
We've hit over 200 of them.
and as far as we can tell.

600
00:55:54.929 --> 00:55:56.681
they're all females.

601
00:55:56.764 --> 00:55:59.517
How about you. Quinn?
You ever seen a male?

602
00:55:59.600 --> 00:56:00.685
I don't know.

603
00:56:00.768 --> 00:56:02.019
When I'm running
for my life.

604
00:56:02.103 --> 00:56:03.771
I don't stop
to look at the plumbing.

605
00:56:03.855 --> 00:56:05.356
Well. we have.

606
00:56:05.440 --> 00:56:08.484
Alex discovered it
about two years back.

607
00:56:08.568 --> 00:56:10.695
She worked out how
the fire in the glands...

608
00:56:10.778 --> 00:56:13.448
Two glands in the mouth
secrete separate chemicals. yep.

609
00:56:13.531 --> 00:56:14.949
That's right.

610
00:56:15.032 --> 00:56:17.702
Combine in exhalation...
nitro-napalm.

611
00:56:17.785 --> 00:56:19.996
Yeah. Well. the chemical
engineer is dead now.

612
00:56:20.079 --> 00:56:21.247
That was his theory.

613
00:56:21.330 --> 00:56:23.541
We figure
they're like fish.

614
00:56:23.624 --> 00:56:25.543
The females spawn the eggs.

615
00:56:25.626 --> 00:56:29.630
One male passes over
and fertilises thousands.

616
00:56:29.714 --> 00:56:31.549
Did you hear what
she said. Quinn?

617
00:56:31.632 --> 00:56:33.342
One male.

618
00:56:33.426 --> 00:56:36.262
That's why we never see any
others. 'cause there's only one.

619
00:56:36.345 --> 00:56:38.014
Now. we tracked the
epidemiology of these things.

620
00:56:38.097 --> 00:56:39.432
and we found out
where they're from.

621
00:56:39.515 --> 00:56:41.142
And that
is why we're here.

622
00:56:41.225 --> 00:56:46.606
We kill the male.
we kill the species.

623
00:56:46.689 --> 00:56:48.483
We're going to London.

624
00:56:48.566 --> 00:56:50.693
Good luck.
It's that way.

625
00:56:50.777 --> 00:56:53.529
No. I need soldiers.

626
00:56:53.613 --> 00:56:56.783
- Quinn. are you listening to me? I need men...
- Men from Pembury went to London.

627
00:56:56.866 --> 00:56:58.993
And maybe she's right because
they disturbed something.

628
00:56:59.076 --> 00:57:00.787
90 of them died.

629
00:57:00.870 --> 00:57:02.789
and then it backtracked them
to their fortress.

630
00:57:02.872 --> 00:57:04.832
And you haven't seen
destruction like that. Van Zan...

631
00:57:04.916 --> 00:57:05.875
not even in this world.

632
00:57:05.958 --> 00:57:07.126
So we walk over dead men...

633
00:57:07.210 --> 00:57:09.003
Not with my people.
you won't!

634
00:57:09.086 --> 00:57:10.922
I've got a castle
full of them.

635
00:57:11.005 --> 00:57:12.799
I'm trying to keep them
alive.

636
00:57:12.882 --> 00:57:15.718
You're just letting them
die slower.

637
00:57:15.802 --> 00:57:17.386
I said no.

638
00:57:17.470 --> 00:57:19.680
I made a mistake letting you
through those gates.

639
00:57:19.764 --> 00:57:21.182
I saw something
in your eyes.

640
00:57:21.265 --> 00:57:22.683
I thought it was awe.
I was wrong.

641
00:57:22.767 --> 00:57:24.811
It's madness.
You're insane.

642
00:57:24.894 --> 00:57:28.064
And I want you out
before you do more damage.

643
00:57:33.653 --> 00:57:35.947
Look out the window.

644
00:57:36.030 --> 00:57:39.075
Eden's not burning.
It's burnt.

645
00:57:48.251 --> 00:57:50.962
Why don't you want to go?

646
00:57:53.714 --> 00:57:56.217
What happened there?

647
00:57:57.969 --> 00:58:02.014
My mother was working on a
railway tunnel... project engineer.

648
00:58:02.098 --> 00:58:04.308
She died there. okay?

649
00:58:07.687 --> 00:58:10.565
You've seen it.
haven't you?

650
00:58:15.153 --> 00:58:17.071
Quinn!

651
00:58:17.155 --> 00:58:19.323
Trouble.

652
00:58:22.326 --> 00:58:24.871
There's nothing magical
about 'em.

653
00:58:24.954 --> 00:58:27.081
They're made up
of a collection of organs.

654
00:58:27.165 --> 00:58:29.208
They have a mind. a heart.
and a liver.

655
00:58:29.292 --> 00:58:31.919
You take out one of these.
you bring down the beast!

656
00:58:37.258 --> 00:58:40.845
Is that it?
Four of you?

657
00:58:42.805 --> 00:58:45.099
Eddie.

658
00:58:45.183 --> 00:58:47.560
Eddie. what you doin'?

659
00:58:47.643 --> 00:58:49.353
You got kids. man.

660
00:58:49.437 --> 00:58:52.857
That's why I'm going.
Creedy. That's why.

661
00:58:56.235 --> 00:58:59.113
The volunteer section of this campaign's
now over. It's time for the draft.

662
00:58:59.197 --> 00:59:01.240
Tito. Mead...

663
00:59:01.365 --> 00:59:02.867
get the six strongest men
they have and load 'em up.

664
00:59:02.950 --> 00:59:04.452
- Right.
- Got it.

665
00:59:04.535 --> 00:59:07.079
Dig your own holes.
Die in 'em.

666
00:59:09.207 --> 00:59:10.917
Oi!

667
00:59:11.000 --> 00:59:12.084
I said no!

668
00:59:12.210 --> 00:59:13.044
No. Quinn!

669
00:59:18.883 --> 00:59:20.510
Get out of my way. Quinn.

670
00:59:56.045 --> 00:59:58.089
Okay. okay.

671
00:59:58.172 --> 01:00:00.299
Get him off!

672
01:00:00.383 --> 01:00:07.014
I'll kill ya!
I'll kill ya!

673
01:00:07.098 --> 01:00:08.349
- That's what we need.
- I'll kill ya!

674
01:00:08.474 --> 01:00:11.394
He's gonna bring it
back here!

675
01:00:11.477 --> 01:00:13.187
Alright.

676
01:00:13.271 --> 01:00:15.982
Alright. he's had enough.

677
01:00:20.820 --> 01:00:22.071
Go. London!

678
01:00:25.825 --> 01:00:27.285
Come on!
Move 'em out!

679
01:00:27.368 --> 01:00:31.539
Come on!
Grab those guys!

680
01:00:38.171 --> 01:00:39.755
You. you. you!

681
01:00:56.063 --> 01:00:57.774
He would have killed you.

682
01:00:57.899 --> 01:00:59.525
He doesn't feel things.

683
01:00:59.609 --> 01:01:03.029
That's the only way
he can do what he does.

684
01:01:05.031 --> 01:01:06.699
Here. Take this.

685
01:01:06.783 --> 01:01:08.034
lodine.

686
01:01:08.159 --> 01:01:11.913
Hurts like hell.
but it kills anything.

687
01:01:40.733 --> 01:01:43.277
Good luck. Quinn.

688
01:02:11.764 --> 01:02:13.891
You too busy
to say goodbye?

689
01:02:13.975 --> 01:02:15.435
You're not my father.

690
01:02:15.518 --> 01:02:17.395
You can't stop me.
Quinn.

691
01:02:17.520 --> 01:02:19.647
I can be an archangel.

692
01:02:19.730 --> 01:02:21.441
Gideon says
he'll teach me.

693
01:02:21.524 --> 01:02:23.151
17 seconds.

694
01:02:23.234 --> 01:02:25.278
Did he tell you
that's how long they live?

695
01:02:25.361 --> 01:02:26.904
Not the good ones.
Gideon's an 8-year veteran.

696
01:02:26.988 --> 01:02:29.282
At least
they're still killing them.

697
01:02:29.365 --> 01:02:33.536
A couple of years. Jared. That's
all I'm asking for. Give me that.

698
01:02:33.619 --> 01:02:36.622
After that. you'll be old
enough. and you can lead 'em.

699
01:02:36.706 --> 01:02:39.333
That's what I want. Out of
everyone. you're the best.

700
01:02:39.417 --> 01:02:41.461
It's a waste of time.
Quinn... all of it.

701
01:02:41.544 --> 01:02:45.798
You're right.
I'm not your father.

702
01:02:45.882 --> 01:02:48.426
I can't... lock you in.
I can't make you stay.

703
01:02:48.509 --> 01:02:51.304
And if you think you're man
enough to speak like that.

704
01:02:51.387 --> 01:02:53.598
then I guess
you're man enough to go.

705
01:03:05.359 --> 01:03:08.780
Goodbye. Jared.

706
01:03:08.905 --> 01:03:11.783
You look after yourself.

707
01:04:41.539 --> 01:04:44.375
That dragon
smells like shit.

708
01:04:44.410 --> 01:04:45.944
Are you gonna burn it?

709
01:04:48.238 --> 01:04:49.406
I love it.

710
01:04:50.699 --> 01:04:52.659
They hate the smell
of their dead.

711
01:04:54.202 --> 01:04:56.162
It's the only thing
that scares 'em.

712
01:04:59.040 --> 01:05:01.001
It might buy us
a couple of days.

713
01:05:11.577 --> 01:05:13.203
Sorry. Quinn.

714
01:05:17.350 --> 01:05:18.518
So am I.

715
01:05:22.689 --> 01:05:24.899
This time I was thinking
I got rid of you for sure.

716
01:07:54.107 --> 01:07:57.193
Van Zan.
what are we doing?

717
01:07:57.318 --> 01:07:59.362
Do you see a way through?

718
01:07:59.487 --> 01:08:01.197
Negative.
It's blocked for miles.

719
01:08:01.280 --> 01:08:02.448
As far as the river.
Denton.

720
01:08:02.573 --> 01:08:03.908
Head back. Alex.

721
01:08:03.991 --> 01:08:06.911
- Find me a way around.
- Copy.

722
01:08:18.881 --> 01:08:21.884
Is this Pembury?

723
01:08:21.968 --> 01:08:23.678
This looks like Pembury.

724
01:08:23.761 --> 01:08:25.221
Do you want to turn back?

725
01:08:25.304 --> 01:08:27.265
Nukes must have done this.

726
01:08:27.390 --> 01:08:28.641
Nukes didn't do this.

727
01:08:28.724 --> 01:08:30.768
Should we set
the triangulators?

728
01:08:35.314 --> 01:08:38.734
No time.

729
01:08:38.860 --> 01:08:41.237
Man the 50-cal.
lock and load.

730
01:08:41.362 --> 01:08:43.239
cut the engines.
and take your positions.

731
01:08:47.910 --> 01:08:50.455
You heard him!
Lock and load!

732
01:08:50.538 --> 01:08:52.123
Let's move! Let's move!

733
01:09:16.814 --> 01:09:18.524
I think it's playing
with us.

734
01:09:18.649 --> 01:09:21.652
It's not playing
with us.

735
01:09:21.736 --> 01:09:23.446
It's setting us up.

736
01:10:12.328 --> 01:10:14.622
Easy. Easy.

737
01:10:14.747 --> 01:10:16.207
Easy. girl.

738
01:10:18.167 --> 01:10:20.461
Van Zan. it's Alex.
Can you read me?

739
01:10:20.545 --> 01:10:23.673
Van Zan.
can you hear me?

740
01:10:25.842 --> 01:10:30.054
Van Zan. if you can hear me.
I'm coming back.

741
01:10:30.138 --> 01:10:32.014
Can anybody hear me?

742
01:10:56.914 --> 01:11:00.168
Van Zan!

743
01:11:00.293 --> 01:11:06.340
Van Zan!

744
01:11:16.642 --> 01:11:18.269
Denton...

745
01:11:18.352 --> 01:11:21.355
What happened?

746
01:11:21.439 --> 01:11:24.776
It was him.

747
01:11:27.236 --> 01:11:30.656
Where are the soldiers?

748
01:11:33.367 --> 01:11:35.828
One pass.

749
01:11:35.912 --> 01:11:39.081
He flew over just once.

750
01:11:43.878 --> 01:11:46.005
The castle.

751
01:12:32.468 --> 01:12:35.430
Get the hell out of there!
Take cover. everybody!

752
01:12:35.513 --> 01:12:36.973
Get it moving!

753
01:12:40.643 --> 01:12:42.478
Anybody upstairs?!

754
01:13:35.740 --> 01:13:39.327
Jared!

755
01:13:40.703 --> 01:13:42.580
- Creedy!
- Quinn!

756
01:13:52.090 --> 01:13:53.508
Have you got them all?

757
01:13:56.219 --> 01:13:58.012
Creedy. help!

758
01:13:58.096 --> 01:14:00.056
I'll get him!
You take her downstairs!

759
01:14:00.181 --> 01:14:04.894
Hurry up! That big boy won't
stop until it's killed us all!

760
01:14:04.977 --> 01:14:07.105
Katie...
she won't move.

761
01:14:07.230 --> 01:14:09.273
Come on. Katie.
Willem. get on my shoulder.

762
01:14:09.357 --> 01:14:12.527
Katie. come on.
Let go of the wall.

763
01:14:12.652 --> 01:14:14.112
Let go. Let go!

764
01:14:25.832 --> 01:14:28.751
Take her! Take her!

765
01:14:37.343 --> 01:14:39.637
Everybody.
move to the back!

766
01:14:39.720 --> 01:14:41.931
I've got all the kids.
Okay. keep pushing up.

767
01:14:42.056 --> 01:14:44.434
Katie's blanket.

768
01:14:56.904 --> 01:14:58.698
Where is everyone?!

769
01:14:58.823 --> 01:15:00.199
Don't you go
up there. Quinn!

770
01:15:00.283 --> 01:15:02.743
There's 65 people up there.
Creedy. I'm going!

771
01:15:02.869 --> 01:15:04.620
God damn it. Quinn.

772
01:15:04.704 --> 01:15:06.831
Don't you dare leave!
It's too dangerous!

773
01:15:06.914 --> 01:15:08.166
I'll clean it up.

774
01:15:08.291 --> 01:15:09.750
Creedy!

775
01:15:21.763 --> 01:15:23.473
Noooo!

776
01:15:28.478 --> 01:15:31.439
Creedy!

777
01:15:32.774 --> 01:15:37.904
No!

778
01:15:57.632 --> 01:16:02.428
- Creedy! -
Creedy! - Creedy!

779
01:16:07.183 --> 01:16:09.393
What do we do
when we wake?

780
01:16:09.477 --> 01:16:13.397
Keep both eyes on the sky.

781
01:16:13.523 --> 01:16:16.150
What do we do...

782
01:16:17.944 --> 01:16:21.030
What do we...

783
01:16:21.114 --> 01:16:23.574
What do we do
when we sleep?

784
01:16:23.658 --> 01:16:27.662
Keep one eye on the sky.

785
01:16:27.745 --> 01:16:30.206
What do we do
when we see him?

786
01:16:30.289 --> 01:16:33.960
Dig hard. dig deep.
run for shelter.

787
01:16:34.043 --> 01:16:37.463
and never look back.

788
01:17:16.627 --> 01:17:19.338
Jared...

789
01:17:21.507 --> 01:17:22.925
We're alive!

790
01:17:23.009 --> 01:17:24.635
We're in here!

791
01:17:24.719 --> 01:17:25.720
Push!

792
01:17:30.641 --> 01:17:32.435
Back away!

793
01:17:57.335 --> 01:17:59.712
You were right.

794
01:18:56.602 --> 01:18:59.397
I salvaged what I could
from your armoury.

795
01:19:01.149 --> 01:19:03.025
We got one rifle.

796
01:19:03.109 --> 01:19:05.236
two automatics.
two crossbows.

797
01:19:05.319 --> 01:19:07.280
and explosive heads.

798
01:19:14.829 --> 01:19:18.082
You. me. and Alex...

799
01:19:18.207 --> 01:19:20.001
down the coast
in the chopper.

800
01:19:20.084 --> 01:19:22.628
Stay tight to the cliffs.

801
01:19:22.712 --> 01:19:25.590
The Thames will take us right
into the heart of London.

802
01:19:25.673 --> 01:19:27.300
I know where he lives.

803
01:19:28.801 --> 01:19:31.637
Magic hour...

804
01:19:31.721 --> 01:19:34.974
You say that's when
they're the weakest.

805
01:19:35.099 --> 01:19:36.642
We'll see.

806
01:19:36.726 --> 01:19:39.896
You're going home.

807
01:19:39.979 --> 01:19:41.814
Jared!

808
01:19:41.898 --> 01:19:43.858
Yeah. Quinn?

809
01:19:46.319 --> 01:19:47.987
You keep them safe.

810
01:21:15.241 --> 01:21:18.327
Well. this town's
gone to hell.

811
01:21:18.411 --> 01:21:20.538
They must have
heard us coming.

812
01:21:20.621 --> 01:21:24.292
What's stopping them?

813
01:21:24.375 --> 01:21:25.376
It's not us.

814
01:21:25.501 --> 01:21:28.337
Either way. we gotta
get in there.

815
01:21:28.421 --> 01:21:31.132
Come on. guys. We're
outnumbered hundreds to 3.

816
01:21:31.215 --> 01:21:34.051
I know this city
from the sky down.

817
01:21:34.135 --> 01:21:36.429
and I know it
from the bottom up.

818
01:21:36.554 --> 01:21:39.474
If we can get in quiet. I can
sneak us into some tunnels.

819
01:21:39.557 --> 01:21:40.725
That should get us close.

820
01:21:45.730 --> 01:21:48.733
Good Christ.

821
01:21:55.448 --> 01:21:57.992
Did he see us?

822
01:22:06.125 --> 01:22:11.464
They must be starving.
They're eating their own.

823
01:22:11.547 --> 01:22:15.718
Oh. we're dead.

824
01:22:15.802 --> 01:22:17.929
Look on the bright side.

825
01:22:18.012 --> 01:22:21.057
<i>Now we've got him
outnumbered 3 to 1.</i>

826
01:22:23.935 --> 01:22:26.854
Now... you ready?

827
01:22:26.938 --> 01:22:28.564
Yeah.

828
01:22:28.689 --> 01:22:30.316
Quinn...

829
01:22:30.441 --> 01:22:33.528
You lead. We follow.

830
01:23:03.474 --> 01:23:05.601
There's an underground
passage...

831
01:23:05.726 --> 01:23:07.770
leads to the
construction site!

832
01:23:07.895 --> 01:23:11.232
Down here!

833
01:23:29.459 --> 01:23:31.419
Clear.

834
01:23:48.478 --> 01:23:51.272
Four tunnels meet
at this shaft.

835
01:23:51.355 --> 01:23:52.982
Leads up to a square. There
used to be buildings up there.

836
01:23:53.107 --> 01:23:54.609
If they're still around.
could be good coverage.

837
01:23:54.692 --> 01:23:56.986
Yeah. if it goes to the street.
that's what we take.

838
01:23:57.111 --> 01:23:58.279
Alex. give me the sticks.

839
01:24:03.993 --> 01:24:06.537
Quinn. these are
highly volatile heads.

840
01:24:06.662 --> 01:24:08.956
You fire them
with your crossbow.

841
01:24:09.040 --> 01:24:11.250
Now. when you...

842
01:24:13.294 --> 01:24:15.338
He knows we're here.
Shh.

843
01:24:15.463 --> 01:24:18.549
Okay.

844
01:24:18.633 --> 01:24:20.384
How tall is that shaft?

845
01:24:20.468 --> 01:24:23.012
150 feet.

846
01:24:23.096 --> 01:24:26.349
Alright.
Here's the plan...

847
01:24:26.474 --> 01:24:29.143
When we get to street level. we gotta
bring that bull's arse to the ground.

848
01:24:29.227 --> 01:24:31.104
and I'm gonna take care
of that.

849
01:24:31.187 --> 01:24:32.980
Now. one shot's gonna kill him.
and it's gonna be with this.

850
01:24:33.064 --> 01:24:35.900
He only exposes his chest
before he breathes fire.

851
01:24:35.983 --> 01:24:38.277
Now. these are magnesium-tip
C-4 arrows.

852
01:24:38.402 --> 01:24:40.238
and they only fly
about 50 feet.

853
01:24:40.321 --> 01:24:42.031
So. when you fire. you gotta
be standing in the furnace.

854
01:24:42.156 --> 01:24:45.034
So do not hesitate.
If you do. we die.

855
01:24:52.250 --> 01:24:54.293
Ah. he's playing
hide-and-seek.

856
01:24:54.419 --> 01:24:57.088
More like cat and mouse.

857
01:25:22.321 --> 01:25:24.365
Quinn!

858
01:25:24.449 --> 01:25:26.742
Use it!

859
01:25:43.801 --> 01:25:46.721
Oh. he's eating it up.

860
01:25:46.804 --> 01:25:49.891
I can't see
a damn thing. Quinn.

861
01:25:49.974 --> 01:25:52.101
What am I looking at?

862
01:25:52.226 --> 01:25:54.979
This is an enclosed square.
It's about 100 metres across.

863
01:25:55.062 --> 01:25:56.898
There's a building right
in the middle.

864
01:25:56.981 --> 01:25:58.941
That chimney looks down
over the lot of it.

865
01:25:59.066 --> 01:26:00.777
What do you think?

866
01:26:02.487 --> 01:26:05.156
I don't know yet.

867
01:26:05.239 --> 01:26:07.992
Hey...

868
01:26:08.075 --> 01:26:09.410
You scared?

869
01:26:10.828 --> 01:26:12.079
No.

870
01:26:12.205 --> 01:26:14.499
It was your idea
to come to London.

871
01:26:15.917 --> 01:26:19.670
Yeah. I thought
I'd be at 3.500 feet.

872
01:26:19.754 --> 01:26:23.007
Yeah. I thought I'd have over
200 men with me right now.

873
01:26:23.132 --> 01:26:27.220
Life's got a funny way of turning
out different. though. don't it?

874
01:26:27.303 --> 01:26:28.471
Yeah.

875
01:26:30.723 --> 01:26:33.684
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

876
01:26:33.768 --> 01:26:36.229
See that railcar?

877
01:26:36.312 --> 01:26:38.439
It'll give us
a better view.

878
01:26:38.564 --> 01:26:41.025
Move.

879
01:26:47.448 --> 01:26:49.826
Drop your packs...
weapons only.

880
01:27:18.020 --> 01:27:20.940
Okay. we're gonna
have a window...

881
01:27:21.023 --> 01:27:24.026
10. maybe 12 seconds every time he
makes a turn. and we're gonna use it.

882
01:27:24.152 --> 01:27:25.736
- How?
- We're gonna split up.

883
01:27:25.820 --> 01:27:28.281
We stay together. take
a hit. and we're gone.

884
01:27:28.364 --> 01:27:30.032
so we gotta use
every angle.

885
01:27:30.116 --> 01:27:32.577
Now. Quinn. you're gonna
take that west wall.

886
01:27:32.702 --> 01:27:35.663
Don't lock and load till
you get there. You got it?

887
01:27:35.746 --> 01:27:37.498
Okay. What about you?

888
01:27:37.582 --> 01:27:39.208
I got the north.

889
01:27:39.333 --> 01:27:42.920
Alex. I need you
to stay right here.

890
01:27:43.045 --> 01:27:45.423
Now. when Quinn and I make a
move. it's gonna draw him off.

891
01:27:45.548 --> 01:27:48.176
and I don't think the
son of a bitch can count.

892
01:27:48.259 --> 01:27:51.179
Now. he's gonna make
another turn.

893
01:27:51.262 --> 01:27:53.723
When he does. I'm
gonna tell you to go.

894
01:27:53.848 --> 01:27:56.976
- You're gonna run like hell to that east wall. Don't think about it...
- It's water!

895
01:27:57.059 --> 01:27:59.520
Keep it.
You're gonna need it.

896
01:28:02.607 --> 01:28:06.861
We have paid
a terrible price.

897
01:28:09.363 --> 01:28:12.700
And now we got a chance
to make a difference.

898
01:28:17.705 --> 01:28:19.332
We will.

899
01:28:39.268 --> 01:28:40.978
Now. that's
our first window.

900
01:28:41.062 --> 01:28:42.063
Quinn...

901
01:28:43.272 --> 01:28:44.649
Move!

902
01:29:22.979 --> 01:29:25.982
The arrows.

903
01:29:56.304 --> 01:29:58.181
Alex!

904
01:29:58.264 --> 01:30:01.184
In about 8 seconds.
we're gonna have a window!

905
01:30:03.478 --> 01:30:05.354
Now. when I tell you
to go.

906
01:30:05.438 --> 01:30:09.984
you run like hell straight
to the base of this chimney!

907
01:30:10.067 --> 01:30:13.821
Are you ready?!

908
01:30:17.784 --> 01:30:20.328
Go! Go!

909
01:30:20.411 --> 01:30:20.995
No!

910
01:30:25.750 --> 01:30:28.461
Run like the wind. baby!

911
01:30:38.763 --> 01:30:39.847
Come on. big boy!

912
01:30:43.893 --> 01:30:45.561
That's right.

913
01:31:22.056 --> 01:31:23.307
Quinn!

914
01:31:24.767 --> 01:31:26.310
Alex!

915
01:31:35.820 --> 01:31:37.864
Stop!

916
01:31:48.124 --> 01:31:49.667
I'm fine.

917
01:31:49.751 --> 01:31:51.461
What are we gonna do?

918
01:31:51.586 --> 01:31:53.463
I lost the explosives.

919
01:31:53.546 --> 01:31:55.298
We're gonna find 'em.

920
01:32:00.094 --> 01:32:01.804
Keep going!

921
01:32:01.888 --> 01:32:03.055
Go around the other side!

922
01:32:03.139 --> 01:32:04.891
I'll slow him down!

923
01:32:35.296 --> 01:32:39.467
He's not moving.
He's waiting for us.

924
01:32:39.550 --> 01:32:42.595
Quinn... by the truck...
the arrow.

925
01:32:42.678 --> 01:32:45.223
By the wheel.

926
01:33:12.333 --> 01:33:14.210
No!

927
01:33:19.006 --> 01:33:20.258
Die!

928
01:34:29.577 --> 01:34:33.790
He always thought
you could do it.

929
01:34:33.873 --> 01:34:37.460
And you did.

930
01:34:42.173 --> 01:34:45.760
Come on.

931
01:35:22.046 --> 01:35:25.550
Quinn! Quinn! Quinn!

932
01:35:25.633 --> 01:35:28.010
We got a signal!
Quinn!

933
01:35:28.136 --> 01:35:29.595
We got a signal.

934
01:35:32.181 --> 01:35:33.891
Well. what's the problem?

935
01:35:33.975 --> 01:35:36.018
They're speaking French.

936
01:35:36.144 --> 01:35:38.688
Well. don't come to me.
I'm lousy at French.

937
01:35:38.813 --> 01:35:40.773
They want to speak
to the person in charge.

938
01:35:40.898 --> 01:35:42.316
Ah...

939
01:35:42.400 --> 01:35:44.444
Well. that would be you.
then.

940
01:35:44.569 --> 01:35:46.779
Just keep 'em talking.

941
01:35:48.906 --> 01:35:51.576
Get us a good bottle
of wine or something.

942
01:35:51.659 --> 01:35:53.202
Go on. now.

943
01:35:53.286 --> 01:35:54.787
Thanks. Quinn.

944
01:35:56.622 --> 01:35:58.040
Go on. all of you.

945
01:35:58.124 --> 01:36:02.170
- Alright. Cheers.
- Well done!

946
01:36:02.253 --> 01:36:05.840
You think it'll last?

947
01:36:05.923 --> 01:36:07.967
I don't know.

948
01:36:08.050 --> 01:36:10.011
It's been. what.
three months

949
01:36:10.136 --> 01:36:12.597
since we saw the last one?

950
01:36:12.722 --> 01:36:17.226
If they come. they'll
burn. we'll build.

951
01:36:17.310 --> 01:36:19.979
Or maybe I'll just
kill 'em.

952
01:36:20.062 --> 01:36:21.314
And here I thought

953
01:36:21.439 --> 01:36:23.900
optimism was against
your nature.

954
01:36:23.983 --> 01:36:26.277
It's a recent development.

955
01:36:30.907 --> 01:36:33.117
Well. here's to evolution.

956
01:37:15.618 --> 01:37:24.710
<i>These embers burn down low</i>

957
01:37:24.836 --> 01:37:33.928
<i>And with my face aglow</i>

958
01:37:34.053 --> 01:37:44.188
<i>You are all I know</i>

959
01:37:44.313 --> 01:37:48.234
<i>Set this place on fire</i>

960
01:37:48.317 --> 01:37:51.904
<i>Let the flames rise higher</i>

961
01:37:51.988 --> 01:37:55.908
<i>And as they reach
the ceiling</i>

962
01:37:55.992 --> 01:37:59.495
<i>At your feet I'm kneeling</i>

963
01:38:07.086 --> 01:38:15.762
<i>Drawing ever near</i>

964
01:38:15.887 --> 01:38:24.228
<i>My cause revealed as clear</i>

965
01:38:24.312 --> 01:38:35.156
<i>Yes. I burn for you here</i>

966
01:38:35.239 --> 01:38:38.993
<i>Set this place on fire</i>

967
01:38:39.077 --> 01:38:42.830
<i>Let the flames rise higher</i>

968
01:38:42.914 --> 01:38:46.751
<i>And as they reach
the ceiling</i>

969
01:38:46.834 --> 01:38:50.755
<i>At your feet I'm kneeling</i>

970
01:38:50.838 --> 01:38:56.636
<i>With every trailing plume</i>

971
01:38:56.719 --> 01:39:01.933
<i>Know it bears me home</i>

972
01:39:04.102 --> 01:39:19.200
<i>Let it burn</i>

973
01:39:42.181 --> 01:39:43.975
<i>Find me</i>

974
01:39:44.058 --> 01:39:45.852
<i>I'm falling</i>

975
01:39:45.935 --> 01:39:49.272
<i>And fooling myself
that it's flight</i>

976
01:39:49.397 --> 01:39:51.524
<i>Imperfect</i>

977
01:39:51.649 --> 01:39:53.276
<i>I plummet</i>

978
01:39:53.359 --> 01:39:55.069
<i>And ponder</i>

979
01:39:55.153 --> 01:39:58.739
<i>Pushed away on principle</i>

980
01:39:58.865 --> 01:40:02.452
<i>Walk away and I stare</i>

981
01:40:02.535 --> 01:40:05.955
<i>Would you stand me up
again?</i>

982
01:40:06.038 --> 01:40:09.792
<i>Wonder if I've said
too much</i>

983
01:40:09.876 --> 01:40:13.921
<i>And we'll never speak again</i>

984
01:40:19.844 --> 01:40:21.304
<i>Forfeit</i>

985
01:40:21.387 --> 01:40:23.139
<i>My future</i>

986
01:40:23.222 --> 01:40:27.059
<i>For feelings
of few far betweens</i>

987
01:40:27.185 --> 01:40:28.686
<i>Mindless</i>

988
01:40:28.770 --> 01:40:30.480
<i>Of merciful</i>

989
01:40:30.563 --> 01:40:32.356
<i>Measures</i>

990
01:40:32.440 --> 01:40:36.277
<i>Making ends preempt
the means</i>

991
01:40:36.402 --> 01:40:39.655
<i>And I searched your eyes
for an answer</i>

992
01:40:39.781 --> 01:40:43.367
<i>And shuddered
at what I found there</i>

993
01:40:43.451 --> 01:40:47.121
<i>As my skin shrunk away
from conclusion</i>

994
01:40:47.246 --> 01:40:50.917
<i>That you lack
the strength to care</i>

995
01:40:51.042 --> 01:40:54.545
<i>Walk away and I stare</i>

996
01:40:54.670 --> 01:40:58.257
<i>Would you stand me up
again?</i>

997
01:40:58.382 --> 01:41:02.136
<i>Wonder if I've said
too much</i>

998
01:41:02.220 --> 01:41:10.103
<i>And we'll never speak
again</i>

999
01:41:10.186 --> 01:41:13.272
<i>Never speak again</i>

1000
01:41:14.305 --> 01:42:14.775
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
